  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study will be comparing the treatment of varicose vein tributaries using either foam
      sclerotherapy or ambulatory phlebectomies. Patients will be randomised to having either
      ambulatory phlebectomy (group A) or foam sclerotherapy (group B) following treatment of their
      saphenous vein.

      The re-intervention rates, safety, patient experience as well as the cost effectiveness of
      each intervention will be assessed.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
